title: Next Gen: Dere types
body:
Ashley- Deredere- Energetic, cheerful always happy. Shows this to everyone, even bad people like Team Skull.

Salvia- Deredere- Energetic, cheerful always happy. Does have calm moments when she’s alone, but still cheerful.

Grey- Tsundere mixed with Kuudere- Cold, hostile on the outside. Nice on the inside. Only close friends see his dere side but even then it’s not much, hence him also being a Kuudere.

Dachi- Himedere- Expected to be treated like royalty. Not to an extreme but still close.

Alex- Dandere- Very shy but warms up after some time.

Dusk- Tsundere- Same as Grey but way more harsh.

Chris- Himedere mixed with Tsundere- Same as Daichi but in an actual relationship he’d be very demanding, Tsundere part is only with Ashley as he refuses to admit he has a crush on her.

Sirius- Hajidere- Blushing type, always blushing near who they like. In Sirius’ case, Ashley.

Natsuko- Bakadere- Clumsy, ditzy and acts like a ten year old in love. When she’s older she gets May’s love of romantic dramas and craves her own, but she gets very clumsy and falls for anyone with a cute face.

Sachihiro- Deredere- Inherts Ash’s energy and denseness when it comes to love. But still is as happy and cheerful as his older sister.

Sachi- Hajidere- When she gets older she’ll inherit Serena’s modesty and shyness more than her sassy side, thus making her blush when she’s near her crush. 

Katri- Kuudere- Not able to talk due to being a mute, but she doesn’t show much emotion aside from a smile. Will still show her dere side with people she’s close to, but most people see her kuu side.

body:
My brother got Pokémon Let’s Go! Pikachu and when I traded with him I found out he’d made his character name “my dude.”

“I was gonna give him my name, but then my friend Nick suggested ‘my dude.’ So now everybody else in the game is like, really chill.”

summary: I saw a tweet that pointed out some things about the naming scheme for Eevee’s different evolutions - Vaporeon Flareon Jolteon...
caption:
I saw a tweet that pointed out some things about the naming scheme for Eevee’s different evolutions -

Vaporeon
Flareon
Jolteon
Espeon

Therefore, Nickelodeon fits.
So here’s an…orange slime Eeeveelution.

I hope one day they include thirtysomething people like me as main characters in pokemon games lol probably in the upcoming detective pikachu film?
